    <h1 class="heading1">Ear, Nose, and Throat (ENT) Department at Aatura Hospital</h1>
    <h4 class="heading4">At Aatura Hospital, our ENT Department offers comprehensive care for conditions affecting the ears, nose, throat, head, and neck. Our team of otolaryngologists (ENT specialists) and allied healthcare professionals are dedicated to providing expert diagnosis, treatment, and management of a wide range of ENT disorders, ensuring optimal outcomes for our patients.</h4>

    <div class="content1">
        <div class="content-left">
            <h3>Our Services</h3>
            <h4>Diagnostic Evaluations</h4>
            <p>We offer comprehensive diagnostic evaluations for patients with ear, nose, and throat disorders, including physical exams, endoscopic evaluations, hearing tests, imaging studies (CT scans, MRI), and laboratory tests. Our ENT specialists utilize advanced diagnostic techniques to accurately assess and diagnose ENT conditions, guiding appropriate treatment plans.</p>

            <h4>Medical and Surgical Treatment</h4>
            <p>We provide both medical and surgical treatment options for various ENT conditions, tailored to meet the individual needs of each patient. Our ENT specialists offer medical management for common conditions such as sinusitis, allergies, ear infections, and voice disorders, as well as surgical interventions for conditions such as tonsillitis, deviated septum, nasal polyps, and hearing loss.</p>

            <h4>Hearing and Balance Disorders</h4>
            <p>We specialize in the diagnosis and treatment of hearing and balance disorders, including conductive hearing loss, sensorineural hearing loss, tinnitus, vertigo, and balance disorders. Our ENT specialists perform audiometric testing, vestibular evaluations, and advanced diagnostic procedures to identify the underlying causes of hearing and balance problems, offering personalized treatment plans to improve functional outcomes.</p>

            <h4>Head and Neck Surgery</h4>
            <p>We offer surgical treatment for head and neck conditions, including thyroid disorders, salivary gland disorders, head and neck tumors, and facial trauma. Our ENT surgeons are skilled in performing minimally invasive and reconstructive procedures, utilizing advanced surgical techniques to achieve optimal functional and cosmetic outcomes for our patients.</p>

            <h4>Pediatric ENT Care</h4>
            <p>We provide specialized care for pediatric patients with ENT conditions, including recurrent ear infections, tonsillitis, adenoid hypertrophy, congenital abnormalities, and speech and language disorders. Our ENT specialists are experienced in managing pediatric ENT conditions with a gentle and compassionate approach, ensuring the comfort and well-being of our young patients.</p>

            <h4>Voice and Swallowing Disorders</h4>
            <p>We evaluate and treat voice and swallowing disorders, including vocal cord nodules, polyps, laryngitis, dysphonia, dysphagia, and gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD). Our ENT specialists perform laryngoscopic examinations, voice assessments, and swallowing studies to diagnose and manage voice and swallowing problems, offering personalized treatment plans to restore vocal function and improve swallowing function.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="content-right"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="content2">
